File: internal/client/providers/device/certificate.go
Package: device
Role: Infrastructure PKI Adapter
Purpose: Manages lifecycle transformations of client-side mTLS credentials, parsing raw text structures into Go TLS primitives and enforcing mandatory ClientAuth validation constraints.

Constants and Vars:
ErrNoPrivateKey, ErrNoCertificate: structural mapping and validation block errors.

Functions:
func LoadDeviceCertificate(certPEM, keyPEM []byte) (tls.Certificate, error). Purpose: construction pipeline. Invokes standard x509 deserialization and triggers strict validateClientCertificate validation rules. Errors: wrapped parsing or extended usage validation errors.
func validateClientCertificate(cert *tls.Certificate) error. Purpose: strict structural enforcement. Ensures certificate leaf slice presence and mandates x509.ExtKeyUsageClientAuth in ExtKeyUsage. Errors: ErrNoCertificate; wrapped x509 parsing error; specific clientAuth missing error.
func EncapsulateDeviceCertificate(cert tls.Certificate) (certPEM, keyPEM []byte, err error). Purpose: serialization pipeline. Encodes all certificate DER structures into standard blocks, marshals target private key components using generic x509.MarshalPKCS8PrivateKey specification formatting. Errors: ErrNoPrivateKey; wrapped PKCS8 marshaling failures.

Security Constraints: Explicitly validates clientAuth usage to shield mTLS gRPC network endpoints from misconfigured, invalid, or unauthorized certificate payloads. Enforces standardized PKCS8 formatting for local encryption wrappers.
